MBOMBELA – Andrè van Eck chased them in his vehicle down Samora Machel Drive and rammed them into another car at the traffic light at Absa Square.  The two suspects then got out of the car and fled the scene.  “They were not armed and I wanted to do a good deed for my community,” Van Eck said.  Van Eck’s white car rammed into the back of the suspects’ car  The driver of the other vehicle, who did not want to be identified out fear that the suspects would use his identity, said he was not mad about what Van Eck did. “He did a good deed and if I was in his shoes I would have done the same thing.”  Martin Jeffreys, Emer-G-Med spokesman, arrived at the scene five minutes after it happened, said nobody got hurt.  Traffic was heavy around the area